WHO   — Herd Immunity — the protective threshold
WHAT  — The population property that protects the few who can't be immune, by denying the disease hosts.
WHERE — POP · Population Dynamics  Framework inputs: ecology, epidemiology, population genetics; Asimov's Foundation; verified & cited  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Life Science)
WHY   — Because a contagion needs susceptible hosts, and past a point it runs out.
HOW   — By immunity (via infection or vaccination) shrinking the susceptible pool below what R₀ needs.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Protect enough of the herd and the disease starves before it reaches the vulnerable. I am a gift the many give the few.

